  "text": "The HotSpot JIT compilation pipeline in OpenJDK is orchestrated through five key C++ header files under src/hotspot/share/. The CompileBroker (src/hotspot/share/compiler/compileBroker.hpp) is the central broker managing all compilation requests, maintaining compile queues and coordinating between the VM and compiler threads. CompilerThread (src/hotspot/share/compiler/compilerThread.hpp) represents the worker threads that execute compilation tasks. The compilation pipeline supports two JIT compiler tiers: the C1 compiler (src/hotspot/share/c1/c1_Compiler.hpp), which is a lightweight first-tier just-in-time compiler, and the C2 compiler (src/hotspot/share/opto/c2compiler.hpp), which is an optimizing JIT compiler that performs aggressive optimizations. Both C1 and C2 inherit from AbstractCompiler (src/hotspot/share/compiler/abstractCompiler.hpp), which defines the common interface and base functionality for all compiler implementations. This hierarchical architecture enables HotSpot to apply profile-guided tiered compilation, starting with fast C1 compilation and transitioning hot methods to the optimizing C2 compiler."
}

